snippet.textDisplay:
I can already see the problem at 6:20 - It's the Costco Eggs. They're bland. They're terrible. You need to go with pastured eggs (the expensive ones with the orange yolks, find a friend with a lot of urban chickens) and Kerrygold Irish Butter. Probably the unsalted butter, because cake science.
Those two things will make literally everything you eat taste 1000% better.
edit- go ahead and get the Kerrygold at Costco. It will be 3-4x expensive everywhere else.
edit 2: Next time, just use traditional waxed dental floss to level off your cakes.
